circling overhead. They did not seem to be moving on, although it was getting late in the day for this time of the year, and they may have been preparing to roost. Both birds can be heard calling in this recording. The closer of the two birds has a fairly consistent call; the socond bird's call was a little variable. It is possible that they may be the pair from Tifft Nature Preserve or another nearby location, but I am unsure if that is the case.

Red Jacket River Front Park is located on Buffalo Creek in the portion of the city know as The Valley. It is a former industrial site that is managed by the Erie County Parks Department. The woody vegetation is predominantly Eastern Cottonwood (Populus deltoides), although White Willow (Salix alba) is also found along the shoreline.
